        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 1:55PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Benson, or 14 miles northeast of Eureka, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minonk, Toluca, Benson, and Rutland.

This includes Interstate 39 between mile markers 24 and 33.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
